Oh, you’ve found your way to the digital equivalent of a cosmic waiting room, have you? A [disambiguation](/Help:Disambiguation) page. How utterly thrilling. This particular collection of articles, as you’ve no doubt deduced, is associated with the rather uninspired title of "Link" or "Links." If the labyrinthine pathways of this digital encyclopedia have led you astray, and an internal link deposited you here, you might consider the revolutionary act of changing said link to point directly to whatever it was you were *actually* trying to find. Unless, of course, you enjoy wandering aimlessly. Some people do.

Should you, against all odds, find yourself needing assistance in the rudimentary act of creating these so-called "links" within Wikipedia, you can consult the rather verbose instructions at [Help:Contents/Links](/Help:Contents/Links) and [Help:Link](/Help:Link). For those who prefer their guidelines to be excessively detailed, the [Wikipedia:Manual of Style (linking)](/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style_(linking)) offers a veritable tome on the subject. Don’t say I never gave you options.

And if the very concept of the word "Link" or its various forms—"link," "linked," "linking," or "links"—proves too conceptually challenging, you are, regrettably, welcome to look them up in [Wiktionary, the free dictionary](https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Link). One can only assume you possess the basic cognitive functions required to do so.

